{"id":14881040,"mediaExerciseId":"c7615607-95a6-4677-8198-4a41a1997c3a","exerciseName":"6","chapterName":"7","chapterTitle":"Interest Rates and Bond Valuation","groupId":612312,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":232,"solutions":[{"id":5976657,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"This task asks **how the issuer determines the bond coupon rate. Then, we should explain the differences between the required return on a bond and the coupon rate.**\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/01/b8a8b1398cdc08de139c345488ea51d8/95d3205eebf2954f5891348767940f00/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/01/b8a8b1398cdc08de139c345488ea51d8/95d3205eebf2954f5891348767940f00/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**The coupon rate determines the issuer of the security**. The bond rate will depend on the maturity of the bond and the riskiness that this bond hold. Before deciding on the bond coupon rate, the issuer analyzes the market interest rates and what other issuers offer for similar security.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/01/b8a8b1398cdc08de139c345488ea51d8/3e913ae8f909a379766f86edd10814f7/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/01/b8a8b1398cdc08de139c345488ea51d8/3e913ae8f909a379766f86edd10814f7/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"**The required return depends on the future investors. It shows how much the investors require for a return to invest in the security.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"hei